<p><strong>Discover the Enchanting World of Narnia with "The Chronicles of Narnia" PDF</strong></p>
<p>J.R.R. Tolkien's "The Lord of the Rings" and C.S. Lewis's "The Chronicles of Narnia" are considered literary masterpieces in the fantasy genre. "The Chronicles of Narnia" is a series of seven books that follow the adventures of different children as they encounter the magical land of Narnia.</p>
<p><strong>1. What is the First Book in the Series?</strong></p>
<p>"The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe" is the first book in "The Chronicles of Narnia" series. It introduces the Pevensie children, Peter, Susan, Edmund, and Lucy, as they discover a magical wardrobe that leads to the enchanted world of Narnia.</p>
<p><strong>2. How Many Books are in the Series?</strong></p>
<p>There are a total of seven books in "The Chronicles of Narnia" series, listed in chronological order of the events they depict:</p>
<ul>
<li>The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe</li>
<li>Prince Caspian</li>
<li>The Voyage of the Dawn Treader</li>
<li>The Silver Chair</li>
<li>The Horse and His Boy</li>
<li>The Magician's Nephew</li>
<li>The Last Battle</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>3. Who is the Author?</strong></p>
<p>Clive Staples Lewis, better known as C.S. Lewis, is the author of "The Chronicles of Narnia" series. He was an English writer, scholar, and lay theologian who also wrote "The Screwtape Letters" and "Mere Christianity."</p>
